ce:section.ce:para:
To prepare the Pc-NGQDs and Pc -NSGQDs, a solution of Pc (10 mg) and GQDs (5 mg) in DMF was prepared and sonicated for 4 h and thereafter stirred at room temperature in the dark for 48 h (
                           Scheme 1

                        ). The conjugates were precipitated and washed using ethanol. For energy dispersive X-ray spectrometer (EDS) spectroscopy, the solid products were used to study the elemental compositions. For UV-vis and Raman spectroscopy, 0.2 mg/ mL of the sensitizers in ultrapure water were prepared for characterization of the sensitizers. For DLS, stock solutions of 0.2 mg/mL were diluted using a dilution factor of 5.

The cellular uptake was determined by measuring the change in fluorescence intensities of the Pc (alone and in the conjugates) and the GQDs at each of the test concentrations. The cells were exposed to the sensitizers and incubated over 24 h. The unabsorbed sensitizers were washed with PBS. The measured changes in fluorescence of the samples with increasing concentrations are shown in Fig. 11
                           . The GQDs, Pc, and conjugates are all taken up by the cells. The cellular uptake increases with an increase in the concentrations for all the sensitizers (Fig. 11
                           ).
